rComments: Literally my favorite prof at UofT! He's an amazing lecturer, hard marker and a very patient with his students. He takes time during his office hours to talk to students and he's a wonderful mentor!

LOVED prof Steele. One of few french profs that really cares and enjoys their job. Go to his office hours for extra help. Seems to know when students are getting lost. Prepares students for all assessment, provides clear feedback on what needs improvement. Wish I could have him for rest of university french

I had this professor for FSL 277. He is very organised and clear, oh yes he can be funny at times, he engages students in class often and is always available for office hours.  I found his oral production tests easier than his theory tests.  Overall, i learned a lot in this course and i would recommend anyone to take this course with him.

GREAT prof! Super organised, very clear, funny, engages students, makes sure everyone understands, and is very available at office hours. Frequent tests which can be stressful, but keeps you on top of things. I had to put more work into this class than other French courses, but so far it has been worth it
He knows his stuff but I found him to be very arrogant. Does not like any kind of talk in his class whatsoever. I wouldn't take this course if I had to choose again.

Has a bit of a anglophone accent which is bad, considering he's teaching Phonetics and Phonology.  Reads off his lecture notes and doesn't make class too interesting.  Gets annoyed if students say anything while he talks.  His section on liason/E caduc is REALLY boring for francophone students.
An organized prof who presents with charts and visuals that greatly helped students understand materials.  Cares about students.
